Jason Njoku, IrokoTV boss, has revealed that he has recovered from the novel Coronavirus.  In an update shared on his Instagram page, Jason who was discharged from the hospital on Saturday November 7, described the disease as ”vicious and relentless.” According to him, the disease has made him the most unwell that he has ever been in his life. ”24th Oct & 7th Nov. Finally leaving the hospital. Can barely walk more than 10m a time but I’m now resting at home. Covid19 is vicious, relentless and made me the most unwell I have ever been in my life. A long recovery ahead. But we thank God” he tweeted 24th Oct & 7th Nov. Finally leaving the hospital. Can barely walk more than 10m a time but I’m now resting at home 🙏🏾. Covid19 is vicious, relentless and made me the most unwell I have ever been in my life. A long recovery ahead. But we thank God 🙏🏾😷. pic.twitter.com/lHrDoVZiRe — JasonNjoku (@JasonNjoku) November 7, 2020 Seun O, the Nigerian photographer who underwent a Coronavirus test after attending the 7th edition of the AMVCA weeks ago, has confirmed that he tested positive for Coronavirus in new Instagram posts he shared. It will be recalled that a documentary producer warned of a suspected case of coronavirus who… April 5, 2020 In "News" Mohammed Abubakar, son of Nigeria’s former vice-president, has narrated what he passed through after spending 40 days in the hospital.Recall that he was recently released after recovering from COVID-19. In March, his father had announced that one of his sons tested positive for the disease after he returned from Switzerland.… April 28, 2020 In "News" Babajide Sanwo-Olu, governor of Lagos, has announced that two coronavirus patients have been discharged. Sanwo-Olu broke the news via his Twitter handle on Monday. “I have more great news for you from our Infectious Disease Hospital, Yaba. Today, two more female patients have recovered fully and have tested negative to… April 6, 2020 In "News"